    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate is headlined by **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (78.13) and **James Wood** (75.23), who both benefit from a highly favorable matchup against Arrighetti and Hudson, respectively. **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** draws a massive +19% boost from the opposing SP\u2019s xERA and a crucial +2% situational lift due to the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery, which maximizes his elite stolen base potential\u2014the primary needle-mover in our league strategy. Similarly, **James Wood** exploits the SP skill advantage at the top of the lineup, capitalizing on his leadoff spot to maximize plate appearances. **Corbin Carroll** (72.54) remains an anchor in our 3-hole; despite facing a competent arm in Michael King, his underlying xwOBA of .372 and the high-leverage lineup placement make him an essential start. **Tyler Soderstrom** (69.65) rounds out our core, benefiting from a favorable platoon split and an ideal 3-hole assignment.\n\nOur bench strategy was defined by a difficult choice regarding **Vinnie Pasquantino** (41.10). While he cleared the 40-point efficiency floor, he was ultimately left out due to a difficult L/L platoon matchup against Reid Detmers and a looming 45% rain risk, which injects too much volatility into our daily game cap management. Conversely, **Trevor Story** (53.55) is started despite a brutal -19% SP skill penalty because his 16% park factor and 4-hole protection provide enough ceiling to ignore the tough matchup against Bradish. We are also monitoring **Luis Campusano**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Trevor Story**, **Seiya Suzuki**, **Jose Caballero**, and **Alex Freeland** closely; all are currently confirmed as \"Lineup Pending.\" Should any of these players be relegated to the bench or shifted significantly down the order by their managers, we will re-evaluate our utility slots immediately to preserve our efficient performance metrics.",
